<paragraph id="8BE56453D964FF9340D9EDE3FC6FF830" blockId="3.[151,1436,1870,2041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D964FF9340D9EDE3FED1F81D" bold="true" box="[199,294,1978,2004]" pageId="3" pageNumber="429">Habitus</emphasis>
: Generally similar to 
<emphasis id="B92EB841D964FF93423BEDE2FD5FF81D" box="[549,680,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="429">
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D964FF93423BEDE2FD53F81D" baseAuthorityName="Yu, Yang &amp; Bu" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[549,676,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latiloba">H. latiloba</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Legs and wing sheaths relatively slightly longer (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D964FF9344F9EDE3FAACF81C" box="[1255,1371,1978,2005]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[181,1410,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[178,1410,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 7. Larvae and adults of two Huosoma species: (a) male larva of H. latiloba; (b) emerging adult male of H. latiloba; (c) mating pair of H. latiloba, Mt. Cangshan, Dali City, Yunnan Province (photo by Guo-Hui Yang); (d) larva of H. tinctipenne ready to feed on the larvae of Chironomidae; (e) final stadium larva of H. tinctipenne; (f) adult female of H. tinctipenne, Yunlong County, Dali City, Yunnan Province (photo by Guo-Hui Yang)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538341/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="429">Figs 7d, e</figureCitation>
) and, caudal lamellae leaf shaped, longer and narrower than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D964FF934306ED86FC66F831" baseAuthorityName="Yu, Yang &amp; Bu" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[792,913,2014,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latiloba">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D964FF934306ED86FC66F831" box="[792,913,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="429">H. latiloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE56453D963FF9440D9EACFFDE2FE64" blockId="4.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D963FF9440D9EACFFEF9FF79" bold="true" box="[199,270,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="430">Head.</emphasis>
Comparatively large, occipital lobes gently rounded, not bulbous in dorsal view; mouthparts (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D963FF94453AEACFFA67FF78" box="[1316,1424,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[160,1412,470,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-146@4.[151,1436,452,1852]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Morphological details of the final stadium larva of H. tinctipenne: (a) prementum, ventral view; (b) same, dorsal view; (c) right labial palp, inner surface; (d) right mandible, posterior view; (e) same, inner surface; (f) left mandible, posterior view; (g) same, inner surface; (h) right maxilla; (i) left maxilla; (j) female ovipositor, ventral view; (k) S8–10 of female, one of lateral lamella absent, lateral view; (l) lateral lamella, lateral view; (m) median lamella, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538335/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="430">Figs 4a–i</figureCitation>
), fairly similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D963FF944153EAE2FE30FF1D" baseAuthorityName="Yu, Yang &amp; Bu" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[333,455,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latiloba">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D963FF944153EAE2FE30FF1D" box="[333,455,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="430">H. latiloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with relatively broader prementum, maximum breadth ca 0.78 length; length about four times wider than base; anterior margin more strongly projected as obtuse isosceles triangle, apex forming 105° angle (dorsal view), with fine marginal denticles; row of four long, strong setae sub-medially on upper side of prementum. Labial palp long and narrow, distinctly expanded apically, upper margin with six very long, strong setae set in raised tooth-like sockets (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D963FF9441E6EB13FD9EFEAC" box="[504,617,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[160,1412,470,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-146@4.[151,1436,452,1852]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Morphological details of the final stadium larva of H. tinctipenne: (a) prementum, ventral view; (b) same, dorsal view; (c) right labial palp, inner surface; (d) right mandible, posterior view; (e) same, inner surface; (f) left mandible, posterior view; (g) same, inner surface; (h) right maxilla; (i) left maxilla; (j) female ovipositor, ventral view; (k) S8–10 of female, one of lateral lamella absent, lateral view; (l) lateral lamella, lateral view; (m) median lamella, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538335/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="430">Figs 4b, c</figureCitation>
); movable hook short, incurved, only ca 1/2 length of longest palpal seta; palp terminating in broad securiform ‘comb’ separated by shallow notch from short ventral hook slightly exceeding margin of comb in length (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D963FF9441DDEBCBFDF0FE64" box="[451,519,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1045,1069]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,643,1012]" captionTargetId="figure-66@5.[151,1435,631,1022]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 6. Labial palp of Huosoma tinctipenne: left, anterior view in situ on prementum; right, showing detail, (a) inner length of comb; (b) width of comb; (c) palpal hook (measurement terminology corresponding with Brochard &amp; van der Ploeg 2013)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538339/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="430">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2534DBD963FF944089ED0DFB79F811" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538335" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6538335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538335/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="430" startId="4.[151,250,1876,1900]" targetBox="[160,1412,470,1836]" targetPageId="4">
