Morphological details of the final stadium larva of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D963FF944336ED0CFC4EF8A5" baseAuthorityName="McLachlan" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[808,953,1877,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tinctipenne">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D963FF944336ED0CFC4EF8A5" box="[808,953,1877,1900]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="430">H. tinctipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (a) prementum, ventral view; (b) same, dorsal view; (c) right labial palp, inner surface; (d) right mandible, posterior view; (e) same, inner surface; (f) left mandible, posterior view; (g) same, inner surface; (h) right maxilla; (i) left maxilla; (j) female ovipositor, ventral view; (k) S8–10 of female, one of lateral lamella absent, lateral view; (l) lateral lamella, lateral view; (m) median lamella, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF2534DBD962FF954089E87BFA80FD96" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538337" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6538337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" startId="5.[151,250,546,570]" targetBox="[163,1426,200,510]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BE56453D962FF954089E87BFA80FD96" blockId="5.[151,1436,546,607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF954089E87BFEE5FDF2" bold="true" box="[151,274,546,571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
Labial palp of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D962FF9541B5E87AFD96FDF3" baseAuthorityName="Yu, Yang &amp; Bu" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[427,609,546,570]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latiloba">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF9541B5E87AFD96FDF3" box="[427,609,546,570]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Huosoma latiloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: left, anterior view in situ on prementum; right, showing detail, (a) inner length of comb; (b) width of comb; (c) palpal hook (measurement terminology corresponding with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB19A2D962FF95443AE81FFA9BFD96" author="Brochard, C. &amp; van der Ploeg, E." box="[1060,1388,582,607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" pagination="159 - 174" refId="ref3059" refString="Brochard, C. &amp; van der Ploeg, E. (2013) Description of the exuvia and larva of Pyrrhosoma elisabethae. Libellula, 32 (3), 159 - 174." type="journal article" year="2013">Brochard &amp; van der Ploeg 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF2534DBD962FF954089EE4CFA65FB9B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538339" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6538339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538339/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" startId="5.[151,250,1045,1069]" targetBox="[162,1423,643,1012]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BE56453D962FF954089EE4CFA65FB9B" blockId="5.[151,1436,1045,1106]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF954089EE4CFEE5FBE4" bold="true" box="[151,274,1045,1069]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
Labial palp of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D962FF9541B7EE4FFD76FBE4" baseAuthorityName="McLachlan" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[425,641,1046,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tinctipenne">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF9541B7EE4FFD76FBE4" box="[425,641,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Huosoma tinctipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: left, anterior view in situ on prementum; right, showing detail, (a) inner length of comb; (b) width of comb; (c) palpal hook (measurement terminology corresponding with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB19A2D962FF95445EEE60FA70FB9B" author="Brochard, C. &amp; van der Ploeg, E." box="[1088,1415,1081,1106]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" pagination="159 - 174" refId="ref3059" refString="Brochard, C. &amp; van der Ploeg, E. (2013) Description of the exuvia and larva of Pyrrhosoma elisabethae. Libellula, 32 (3), 159 - 174." type="journal article" year="2013">Brochard &amp; van der Ploeg 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE56453D962FF9540D9EED9FB7CFB76" blockId="5.[151,1437,1152,1574]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF9540D9EED9FED0FB53" bold="true" box="[199,295,1152,1178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Thorax.</emphasis>
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D962FF9541C9EED9FDB8FB53" baseAuthorityName="Yu, Yang &amp; Bu" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[471,591,1152,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latiloba">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF9541C9EED9FDB8FB53" box="[471,591,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">H. latiloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but legs longer; femur of hind leg reaching to hind margin of S4; outer wing sheaths reaching just beyond hind margin of S4, inner sheaths slightly shorter (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D962FF954415EEFDFB89FB76" box="[1035,1150,1188,1215]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[181,1410,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[178,1410,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 7. Larvae and adults of two Huosoma species: (a) male larva of H. latiloba; (b) emerging adult male of H. latiloba; (c) mating pair of H. latiloba, Mt. Cangshan, Dali City, Yunnan Province (photo by Guo-Hui Yang); (d) larva of H. tinctipenne ready to feed on the larvae of Chironomidae; (e) final stadium larva of H. tinctipenne; (f) adult female of H. tinctipenne, Yunlong County, Dali City, Yunnan Province (photo by Guo-Hui Yang)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Figs 7d–e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE56453D962FF9540D9EE9EFCF8FA87" blockId="5.[151,1437,1152,1574]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF9540D9EE9EFEB4FB28" bold="true" box="[199,323,1223,1249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D962FF9541ECEE91FD9DFB2B" baseAuthorityName="Yu, Yang &amp; Bu" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[498,618,1224,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latiloba">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF9541ECEE91FD9DFB2B" box="[498,618,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">H. latiloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but ovipositor of female extending only to end of S10 (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D962FF9544D3EE91FACBFB2A" box="[1229,1340,1224,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[160,1412,470,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-146@4.[151,1436,452,1852]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Morphological details of the final stadium larva of H. tinctipenne: (a) prementum, ventral view; (b) same, dorsal view; (c) right labial palp, inner surface; (d) right mandible, posterior view; (e) same, inner surface; (f) left mandible, posterior view; (g) same, inner surface; (h) right maxilla; (i) left maxilla; (j) female ovipositor, ventral view; (k) S8–10 of female, one of lateral lamella absent, lateral view; (l) lateral lamella, lateral view; (m) median lamella, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538335/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Figs 4j–k</figureCitation>
). Caudal lamellae foliate, long and narrow, more than half length of abdomen (maximum length 3.5 times width of lateral lamella and 3.2 times width of median lamella (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D962FF9542ACEF49FCDDFAE2" box="[690,810,1296,1323]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[160,1412,470,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-146@4.[151,1436,452,1852]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Morphological details of the final stadium larva of H. tinctipenne: (a) prementum, ventral view; (b) same, dorsal view; (c) right labial palp, inner surface; (d) right mandible, posterior view; (e) same, inner surface; (f) left mandible, posterior view; (g) same, inner surface; (h) right maxilla; (i) left maxilla; (j) female ovipositor, ventral view; (k) S8–10 of female, one of lateral lamella absent, lateral view; (l) lateral lamella, lateral view; (m) median lamella, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538335/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Figs 4l–m</figureCitation>
). Lateral lamellae white-tipped with short terminal filament, also present in median lamella but less developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34037D8D962FF9540D9EF01FD35F9EF" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE56453D962FF9540D9EF01FF29FA73" blockId="5.[151,1437,1152,1574]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF9540D9EF01FE3FFAB8" bold="true" box="[199,456,1367,1394]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Larvae (N=3), body length (excluding caudal lamellae) 11.5–14; length of abdomen (excluding caudal lamellae) 7.5–8; maximum head width 2.8–2.9; length of hind femur 3.6–4; lateral caudal lamella 4.5–5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE56453D962FF9540D9EF9AFD35F9EF" blockId="5.[151,1437,1152,1574]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF9540D9EF9AFE7EFA17" bold="true" box="[199,393,1475,1502]" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Biological notes.</emphasis>
The larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A1FD0D962FF954236EF9DFD32FA14" baseAuthorityName="McLachlan" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[552,709,1476,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Huosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tinctipenne">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D962FF954236EF9DFD32FA14" box="[552,709,1476,1501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">H. tinctipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in a small, heavily vegetated shallow pond in a brook at an elevation of approximately 
<quantity id="4CA2C9B6D962FF954215EFBEFD90F9CB" box="[523,615,1511,1538]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" pageId="5" pageNumber="431" unit="m" value="2550.0">2,550 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="136178D6D962FF954269EFB1FD3DF9CA" box="[631,714,1512,1539]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,181,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[158,1429,181,1938]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 8. Habitats of the larvae of two Huosoma species in Yunnan: (a) H. latiloba; (b) H. tinctipenne." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538343/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Fig. 8b</figureCitation>
). Adults were often present breeding in the same pond (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D962FF95455EEFB1FA78F9CA" box="[1344,1423,1512,1539]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[181,1410,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[178,1410,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 7. Larvae and adults of two Huosoma species: (a) male larva of H. latiloba; (b) emerging adult male of H. latiloba; (c) mating pair of H. latiloba, Mt. Cangshan, Dali City, Yunnan Province (photo by Guo-Hui Yang); (d) larva of H. tinctipenne ready to feed on the larvae of Chironomidae; (e) final stadium larva of H. tinctipenne; (f) adult female of H. tinctipenne, Yunlong County, Dali City, Yunnan Province (photo by Guo-Hui Yang)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="431">Fig. 7f</figureCitation>
). The flight season ranges from June to September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
